He took a long sip of whiskey, and, rinsing his mouth with it in a manner Person had never yet witnessed, very slowly replaced his glass on the low table. Then, –ê deux with the muzzled stuff, he swallowed it and shifted to his second English style, the grand one of his most memorable characters:

